{"title_page": "Salute Your Shorts", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Salute Your Shorts\n| image = SaluteYOurShorts.png\n| caption = Title Card\n| runtime = 30 minutes\n| creator = Steve Slavkin\n| executive_producer =\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Kirk Baily]]\n* Megan Berwick\n* [[Michael Ray Bower|Michael Bower]]\n* [[Danny Cooksey]]\n* Venus DeMilo\n* [[Trevor Eyster|Tim Eyster]]\n* [[Heidi Lucas]]\n* Erik MacArthur\n* [[Blake Sennett|Blake Soper]]\n* Steve Slavkin\n}}\n| narrated = Jordan G. Smith\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| company = [[Propaganda Films]]<ref name=\"production\">{{cite web |author=<!-- Staff report --> |url=https://variety.com/1991/tv/features/nickelodeon-99126520/ |title=Nickelodeon |work=Variety |date=May 6, 1991 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>\n| distributor = [[CBS Television Distribution]]\n| network = [[Nickelodeon]]\n| first_aired = {{Start date|1991|7|4}}<ref name=\":1\" />\n| last_aired = {{End date|1992|6|29}}\n| num_episodes = 26\n| num_seasons = 2\n| list_episodes = List of Salute Your Shorts episodes\n| website = http://www.nicksplat.com/social-wall/salute-your-shorts\n}}\n\n'''''Salute Your Shorts''''' is an [[United States|American]] [[comedy]] [[Original television series|television series]] that aired on [[Nickelodeon]] from 1991 to 1992 with reruns until early 1999. It was based on the 1986 book ''Salute Your Shorts: Life at Summer Camp'' by Steve Slavkin and Thomas Hill.\n\nThe series is set at the fictional [[summer camp]], Camp Anawanna. It focuses on teenage campers, their strict and bossy counselor, and the various capers and jocularities they engage in.  It was primarily filmed at [[Franklin Canyon Park]] and the Griffith Park Boys Camp within [[Griffith Park]] in [[Los Angeles]].\n\nThe title comes from a common [[prank]] campers play on each other: a group of children steal a boy's [[boxer shorts]] and raise them up a flagpole. Hence, when people see them waving like a flag, other children salute them as part of the prank.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Kirk Baily]] as Kevin \"Ug\" Lee, head camp counselor\n* Megan Berwick as Z.Z. Ziff\n* [[Michael Ray Bower|Michael Bower]] as Eddie C. \"Donkeylips\" Gelfand\n* Venus DeMilo as Telly Radford\n* [[Trevor Eyster|Tim Eyster]] as Sponge Harris \n* [[Heidi Lucas]] as Dina Alexander\n* Erik MacArthur as Michael Stein {{small|(season 1)}}\n* [[Blake Sennett|Blake Soper]] as Ronald \"Ronnie\" Foster Pinsky {{small|(season 2)}}\n* [[Danny Cooksey]] as Robert \"Bobby\" Budnick\n* Steve Slavkin as Dr. Kahn, the [[unseen character|unseen]] camp director\n\n== Cancellation ==\nThe series was not renewed for a third season due to budgetary disputes and most of the cast unwilling to relocate from [[Los Angeles]] to [[Orlando]], the home of [[Nickelodeon Studios]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/769192/salute-your-shorts-turns-25-here-s-everything-you-may-not-have-known-about-your-fave-childhood-show|title=Everything You May Not Have Known About Salute Your Shorts|newspaper=E! Online|access-date=2017-02-07|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Main|List of Salute Your Shorts episodes}}\n{{:List of Salute Your Shorts episodes}}\n\nThe pilot for the series aired as a special on Nickelodeon in October 1990.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web |first=Susan|last=King |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-06-16/news/tv-1197_1_summer-camp |title=Summer Sights |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=June 16, 1991 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Lauren|last=Lipton |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-07-07/news/tv-2800_1_camp-anawanna |title=Camp out with Nick as 'Salute Your Shorts' returns as weekend series |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=July 7, 1991 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref> After the pilot episode was picked up to series, all of the actors had to re-audition for their roles.<ref>{{cite web|last=Greene |first=James |url=http://www.ink19.com/issues/march2006/interviews/michaelRayBower.html |title=Michael Ray Bower |work=Ink 19 |date= |accessdate=2010-05-11}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nThe series was the second highest rated cable TV series in kids 6\u201311 during its second season.<ref name=\"S2-marathon\">{{cite web |first1=Susan|last1=King |first2=Nadine|last2=Mendoza |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1992-06-21/news/tv-1177_1_p-s-camp |title=Camp out for 7 hours with Nickelodeon's 'Salute Your Shorts' |work=Los Angeles Times |date=June 21, 1992 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref> Despite having not aired new episodes in four years, ''Salute Your Shorts'' was among the top 15 highest-rated, regularly scheduled basic-cable series in 1996 according to ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref>{{cite web |first=Ray|last=Richmond |url=https://variety.com/1997/tv/ratings/numbers-game-puts-nick-way-out-front-1117433320/ |title=Numbers game puts Nick way out front |work=Variety |date=January 19, 1997 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>\n\n== Availability ==\nIn March 2010, six episodes from season two became available for purchase on [[iTunes]], [[Amazon.com]], and [[Zune]] marketplace. In August 2010, six episodes from season one became available for purchase on each place. Six episodes are also available on [[Media Go]]. As of May of 2018 (when [[tvshowsondvd.com]] shut down their website in favor of social-media posts only), the series was the #1 voted show that had yet to see a physical release of a full season in all of television.\n\n''Salute Your Shorts'' has appeared frequently on [[The Splat]], formerly The 90s Are All That, a 1990s oriented program block on [[TeenNick]]. Because of the series' relatively short run, the series does not have a permanent time slot, but it has won several U-Picks and has also appeared in holiday blocks.\n\n== Reunions ==\nMany of the original cast and crew reunited in September 2012 for a panel at the [[Comikaze Expo]] in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.waldenponders.com/salute-your-shorts-reunion.html|title=\"Salute Your Shorts\" Reunion|website=waldenponders}}</ref> \n\nAnother reunion occurred in 2015 with most of the cast attending Portland\u2019s Everything Is Festival. Danny Cooksey did not attend as he was recording an album with country and western band Shelter Dogs.<ref>{{cite web |first=Kelly|last=Connolly |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/06/01/salute-your-shorts-cast-reunites |title=Salute Your Shorts cast reunites\u2014and Donkeylips sings the theme song |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=June 1, 2015 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n* 1993 \u2014 Award - Best Young Actor Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Michael Ray Bower|Michael Bower]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Fourteenth Annual Youth in Film Awards|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/pastnoms14.htm|publisher=Young Artist Awards|accessdate=2014-06-28}}</ref>\n* 1993 \u2014 Award - Best Young Actress Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Heidi Lucas]])\n* 1993 \u2014 Nomination - Best Young Actor Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Danny Cooksey]])\n* 1993 \u2014 Nomination - Best Young Actress Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s (Venus DeMilo)\n* 1993 \u2014 Nomination - Best Young Actor Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Trevor Eyster|Tim Eyster]])\n\nThe series was also [[ACE Award]]-nominated.<ref name=\"S2-marathon\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb title|id=0101190|title=Salute Your Shorts}}\n* {{tv.com show|salute-your-shorts|Salute Your Shorts}}\n\n{{Former Nickelodeon original series}}\n\n[[Category:1990s American comedy-drama television series]]\n[[Category:1990s American teen drama television series]]\n[[Category:1990s American teen sitcoms]]\n[[Category:1990s Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:1991 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1992 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series about summer camps]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on books]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed in Los Angeles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Salute Your Shorts\n| image = SaluteYOurShorts.png\n| caption = Title Card\n| runtime = 30 minutes\n| creator = Steve Slavkin\n| executive_producer =\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Kirk Baily]]\n* Megan Berwick\n* [[Michael Ray Bower|Michael Bower]]\n* [[Danny Cooksey]]\n* Venus DeMilo\n* [[Trevor Eyster|Tim Eyster]]\n* [[Heidi Lucas]]\n* Erik MacArthur\n* [[Blake Sennett|Blake Soper]]\n* Steve Slavkin\n}}\n| narrated = Jordan G. Smith\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| company = [[Propaganda Films]]<ref name=\"production\">{{cite web |author=<!-- Staff report --> |url=https://variety.com/1991/tv/features/nickelodeon-99126520/ |title=Nickelodeon |work=Variety |date=May 6, 1991 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>\n| distributor = [[CBS Television Distribution]]\n| network = [[Nickelodeon]]\n| first_aired = {{Start date|1991|7|4}}<ref name=\":1\" />\n| last_aired = {{End date|1992|6|29}}\n| num_episodes = 26\n| num_seasons = 2\n| list_episodes = List of Salute Your Shorts episodes\n| website = http://www.nicksplat.com/social-wall/salute-your-shorts\n}}\n\n'''''Salute Your Shorts''''' is an [[United States|American]] [[comedy]] [[Original television series|television series]] that aired on [[Nickelodeon]] from 1991 to 1992 with reruns until early 1999. It was based on the 1986 book ''Salute Your Shorts: Life at Summer Camp'' by Steve Slavkin and Thomas Hill.\n\nThe series is set at the fictional [[summer camp]], Camp Anawanna. It focuses on teenage campers, their strict and bossy counselor, and the various capers and jocularities they engage in.  It was primarily filmed at [[Franklin Canyon Park]] and the Griffith Park Boys Camp within [[Griffith Park]] in [[Los Angeles]].\n\nThe title comes from a common [[prank]] campers play on each other: a group of children steal a boy's [[boxer shorts]] and raise them up a flagpole. Hence, when people see them waving like a flag, other children salute them as part of the prank.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Kirk Baily]] as Kevin \"Ug\" Lee, head camp counselor\n* Megan Berwick as Z.Z. Ziff\n* [[Michael Ray Bower|Michael Bower]] as Eddie C. \"Donkeylips\" Gelfand\n* Venus DeMilo as Telly Radford\n* [[Trevor Eyster|Tim Eyster]] as Sponge Harris \n* [[Heidi Lucas]] as Dina Alexander\n* Erik MacArthur as Michael Stein {{small|(season 1)}}\n* [[Blake Sennett|Blake Soper]] as Ronald \"Ronnie\" Foster Pinsky {{small|(season 2)}}\n* [[Danny Cooksey]] as Robert \"Bobby\" Budnick\n* Steve Slavkin as Dr. Kahn, the [[unseen character|unseen]] camp director\n\n== Cancellation ==\nThe series was not renewed for a third season due to budgetary disputes and most of the cast unwilling to relocate from [[Los Angeles]] to [[Orlando]], the home of [[Nickelodeon Studios]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/769192/salute-your-shorts-turns-25-here-s-everything-you-may-not-have-known-about-your-fave-childhood-show|title=Everything You May Not Have Known About Salute Your Shorts|newspaper=E! Online|access-date=2017-02-07|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{Main|List of Salute Your Shorts episodes}}\n{{:List of Salute Your Shorts episodes}}\n\nThe pilot for the series aired as a special on Nickelodeon in October 1990.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web |first=Susan|last=King |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-06-16/news/tv-1197_1_summer-camp |title=Summer Sights |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=June 16, 1991 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Lauren|last=Lipton |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1991-07-07/news/tv-2800_1_camp-anawanna |title=Camp out with Nick as 'Salute Your Shorts' returns as weekend series |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=July 7, 1991 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref> After the pilot episode was picked up to series, all of the actors had to re-audition for their roles.<ref>{{cite web|last=Greene |first=James |url=http://www.ink19.com/issues/march2006/interviews/michaelRayBower.html |title=Michael Ray Bower |work=Ink 19 |date= |accessdate=2010-05-11}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nThe series was the second highest rated cable TV series in kids 6\u201311 during its second season.<ref name=\"S2-marathon\">{{cite web |first1=Susan|last1=King |first2=Nadine|last2=Mendoza |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1992-06-21/news/tv-1177_1_p-s-camp |title=Camp out for 7 hours with Nickelodeon's 'Salute Your Shorts' |work=Los Angeles Times |date=June 21, 1992 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref> Despite having not aired new episodes in four years, ''Salute Your Shorts'' was among the top 15 highest-rated, regularly scheduled basic-cable series in 1996 according to ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref>{{cite web |first=Ray|last=Richmond |url=https://variety.com/1997/tv/ratings/numbers-game-puts-nick-way-out-front-1117433320/ |title=Numbers game puts Nick way out front |work=Variety |date=January 19, 1997 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>\n\n== Availability ==\nIn March 2010, six episodes from season two became available for purchase on [[iTunes]], [[Amazon.com]], and [[Zune]] marketplace. In August 2010, six episodes from season one became available for purchase on each place. Six episodes are also available on [[Media Go]]. As of May of 2018 (when [[tvshowsondvd.com]] shut down their website in favor of social-media posts only), the series was the #1 voted show that had yet to see a physical release of a full season in all of television.\n\n''Salute Your Shorts'' has appeared frequently on [[The Splat]], formerly The 90's Are All That a 1990s oriented program block on [[TeenNick]]. Because of the series' relatively short run, the series does not have a permanent time slot, but it has won several U-Picks and has also appeared in holiday blocks.\n\n== Reunions ==\nMany of the original cast and crew reunited in September 2012 for a panel at the [[Comikaze Expo]] in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.waldenponders.com/salute-your-shorts-reunion.html|title=\"Salute Your Shorts\" Reunion|website=waldenponders}}</ref> \n\nAnother reunion occurred in 2015 with most of the cast attending Portland\u2019s Everything Is Festival. Danny Cooksey did not attend as he was recording an album with country and western band Shelter Dogs.<ref>{{cite web |first=Kelly|last=Connolly |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/06/01/salute-your-shorts-cast-reunites |title=Salute Your Shorts cast reunites\u2014and Donkeylips sings the theme song |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=June 1, 2015 |accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n* 1993 \u2014 Award - Best Young Actor Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Michael Ray Bower|Michael Bower]])<ref>{{cite web|title=Fourteenth Annual Youth in Film Awards|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/pastnoms14.htm|publisher=Young Artist Awards|accessdate=2014-06-28}}</ref>\n* 1993 \u2014 Award - Best Young Actress Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Heidi Lucas]])\n* 1993 \u2014 Nomination - Best Young Actor Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Danny Cooksey]])\n* 1993 \u2014 Nomination - Best Young Actress Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s (Venus DeMilo)\n* 1993 \u2014 Nomination - Best Young Actor Co-Starring in a Cable Series \u2014 [[Young Artist Award]]s ([[Trevor Eyster|Tim Eyster]])\n\nThe series was also [[ACE Award]]-nominated.<ref name=\"S2-marathon\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb title|id=0101190|title=Salute Your Shorts}}\n* {{tv.com show|salute-your-shorts|Salute Your Shorts}}\n\n{{Former Nickelodeon original series}}\n\n[[Category:1990s American comedy-drama television series]]\n[[Category:1990s American teen drama televi